value.title: Graham: 'I could not disagree more' with Trump support of Afghanistan troop withdrawal
value.excerpt: Lindsey Graham (R-S.C.) on Sunday pushed back on former President Trump 's support for removing all troops from Afghanistan, writing on Twitter that he “could not disagree more with former President Trump regarding his support for President Biden ’s withdrawal of all forces from Afghanistan against sound military advice.

value.title: Babylon Bee editor in chief scolds Samantha Bee for pulling punches on Biden: 'Blinded by your own worldview'
value.excerpt: The editor-in-chief of the popular satirical website The Babylon Bee sounded off at TBS’ far-left "Full Frontal" host Samantha Bee over the weekend after she admitted to going easy on President Biden despite years of hard-hitting jokes at the expense of his predecessor.

value.title: Washington Post: Trump-installed NSA lawyer resigns after being on administrative leave for three months
value.excerpt: National Security Agency general counsel Michael Ellis, who was installed by Trump officials in the final days of the administration, resigned from his post on Friday after being on administrative leave since the start of the Biden administration, according to The Washington Post.

value.title: Blinken says it will be 'very hard to meet' Biden's pledge to resettle 62,000 refugees
value.excerpt: Secretary of State Antony Blinken on Sunday said it will be "very hard to meet" President Biden's pledge to resettle 62,000 refugees by the end of the fiscal year.

value.title: GOP White House hopefuls move forward as Trump considers run

value.title: John Ratcliffe: America's adversaries are 'testing', 'taking advantage of' Biden 'wrong decisions'
value.excerpt: President Biden's national security and foreign policy moves are "failing" early in his administration, former Director of National Intelligence John Ratcliffe told "Life, Liberty & Levin" in an interview airing Sunday night.

value.title: Biden takes on Democrats’ ‘Mission Impossible’: Revitalizing coal country
value.excerpt: Despite deep skepticism from union allies, Democrats are determined to make their “Just Transition” away from fossil fuels work.

value.title: Biden describes border surge as a ‘crisis’ as he defends refugee moves
value.excerpt: President Biden on Saturday described the situation at the border as a “crisis” for the first time, as he defended his administration’s walkback on refugee policy a day earlier.

value.title: White House tells refugee advocates Biden likely to raise cap quickly
value.excerpt: White House officials signaled in a conference call with refugee resettlement advocates late Friday that President Joe Biden is likely to raise the current refugee cap of 15,000 quickly, well ahead of the May 15 deadline set Friday, according to a person familiar with the matter.

value.title: Lawyers: DOJ defense in Trump defamation suit is 'dangerous'
value.excerpt: Lawyers for a woman who is suing former President Donald Trump say the U.S. Justice Department made a “wrong and dangerous” argument in seeking to defend him

value.title: Florida woman charged for allegedly threatening to kill Kamala Harris
value.excerpt: A Miami woman has been charged for allegedly threatening to kill Vice President Kamala Harris, according to a criminal complaint filed in the United States District Court for the Southern District of Florida.

value.title: Swipes at China as Joe Biden and Japanese PM seek united front in Asia Pacific
value.excerpt: In his first in-person summit since taking office, the US president hosts Yoshihide Suga as part of efforts to face down Beijing

value.title: Biden says Iran enriching uranium at 60% is not helpful, but is pleased country engaging in indirect talks
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden on Friday said Iran's decision to enrich uranium at 60% is not helpful and counter to the agreement the countries made under the Iran nuclear deal, but said he is pleased the country continues to engage in indirect talks with the United States.

value.title: Fox Nation takes a look at taxes: How Trump, Cuomo and the Rolling Stones have shaped the taxation debate
value.excerpt: In the fifth, and final, episode of Fox Nation's special "An Unauthorized History of Taxes," anchor Bret Baier and his guest experts explore the contemporary state of taxation, and its cause-and-effect.

value.title: Biden says US, Japan 'committed to working together' on challenges from China, North Korea
value.excerpt: President Biden on Friday said he and Japanese Prime Minister Yoshihide Suga affirmed their “ironclad support” of the U.S.-Japanese alliance, saying the two nations committed to take on challenges posed by China and North Korea together to “ensure a future of a free and open Indo-Pacific.”

value.title: Trump National Security Advisor commends Biden Administration: 'No more important alliance' than Japan
value.excerpt: Former National Security Advisor under President Trump, Robert O'Brien, discusses Biden's response to tension with China and Russia.

value.title: Oath Keeper Becomes First to Plead Guilty in Pro-Trump Capitol Riot
value.excerpt: Jon Schaffer of Indiana admits to carrying bear spray and obstructing official proceedings.

value.title: Senate Dems call on Biden to close Guantanamo to advance 'universal rights'
value.excerpt: Sen. Majority Whip Dick Durbin, D-Ill., and Sen. Patrick Leahy, D-Vt., wrote a letter along with 22 other Democrats to President Biden asking him to shut down the military prison in Guantanamo Bay.

value.title: Pro-Trump lawmakers form caucus to promote 'Anglo-Saxon political traditions'

value.title: Trump EPA appointee blocked public release of cancer danger, inspector general says
value.excerpt: Trump administration political appointees at the Environmental Protection Agency repeatedly squashed efforts to warn the public about a cancer-causing gas in their neighborhood, according to a new review.

value.title: Kamala Harris cited Russian bounty story in general election debate with Pence
value.excerpt: Vice President Harris cited the now-backpedaled report of Russia placing bounties on the heads of U.S. soldiers during a general election debate in October with former Vice President Mike Pence.

value.title: AG Merrick Garland rescinds a Trump-era memo curtailing consent decrees in investigations of police departments
value.excerpt: The memo comes as the Justice Department shifts its priorities to focus more on civil rights issues, criminal justice overhauls and policing policies.

value.title: Mike Pence undergoes surgery to have pacemaker implanted
value.excerpt: "The routine surgery was successful, and he is expected to fully recover and return to normal activity in the coming days," Pence's office said.
